  year = {1975},
  volume = {2},
  number = {1},
  pages = {287--300},
  doi = {10.1007/bf00212739},
  note = {
  CORE ARGUMENT: Habermas proposes a reconstruction of historical materialism
  that separates the evolutionary development of normative structures (moral-
  practical learning) from the development of productive forces (technical-
  cognitive learning). This reconstructed historical materialism incorporates
  Weber's insights about the differentiation of value spheres while grounding
  the logic of development in communicative competence rather than labor.

  RELEVANCE: This early programmatic text is where Habermas first articulates
