  distinguishing his approach from both Marx and Weber. The Weber-Marx axis
  is explicitly at issue, making this essential for understanding the
  Habermas-Weber dimension of the philosophy-of-history debate.

  POSITION: Programmatic -- lays out the agenda for Habermas's reconstructive
  theory of history that Theory of Communicative Action would later execute.
  },
  keywords = {Habermas, historical-materialism, social-evolution, Weber, Marx, developmental-history, High, INCOMPLETE, no-abstract}
}

